<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-09-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-09-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="286" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d286">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Cridler</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Goodnow</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-11"><hi rend="italic">September 11,
                                        1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 218.]</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of
                                your dispatch No. 285, of the 2d ultimo, in regard to the refusal of
                                the Tsungli Yamen to deliver your cipher message to Minister Conger,
                                and to express the Department’s approval of your actions in the
                                premises.</p>
                            <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Thos. W. Cridler</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Third Assistant
                                Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>